The President expresses his condolences for the crash of a military C-130 from the North Carolina Air National Guard while supporting firefighting efforts in South Dakota. The crew and their families are in his thoughts and prayers. He praises the men and women who risk their lives to fight these wildfires and acknowledges their heroic efforts. He also expresses concern for the surviving crew members and offers his deepest gratitude to all those involved in the fight against the wildfires.